PN,34201
SC,0001
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F342A1670850422
OL,5,GDigital switchover involved moving
OL,6,Gusers from one universal free-to-access
OL,7,Gservice to another. There's no such
OL,8,Gequivalent yet for an IP-switchover.
OL,10,FOf the relatively new online-only
OL,11,Fservices from Sky, Virgin Media O2 and
OL,12,FBT, all force viewers to use a specific
OL,13,Freceiving device and two of them force
OL,14,Fusers on to the provider's broadband
OL,15,Fservice and router.
OL,3,CState of play: a UK IP-TV switchover
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S     G1/13
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34202
SC,0002
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F342A1670850422
OL,5,FOnce locked into using the devices, the
OL,6,Fproviders are able to charge for any
OL,7,Ffeature they like: Sky charges #5 to
OL,8,Factivate the fast forward button during
OL,9,Fadverts on on-demand content via Sky
OL,10,FGlass/Sky Stream. Providers can also
OL,11,Fbind consumers into contracts with
OL,12,Fabove inflation rises.
OL,3,CState of play: a UK IP-TV switchover
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S     G2/13
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34203
SC,0003
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F342A1670850422
OL,5,FSome providers boldly advertise that
OL,6,Ftheir TV services are available on a
OL,7,Frolling monthly basis ` stop anytime,
OL,8,Fno commitment! They might not be so
OL,9,Fforthcoming about any linked services
OL,10,Fthat are subject to a contract and the
OL,11,Ffact if you do cancel, your smarter
OL,12,Fthan smart TV will go dumber than a
OL,13,Fdumb TV.
OL,15,FFreeview Play and Freesat's connected
OL,16,FTV boxes are a start, but the service
OL,17,Fis still pinned on reception via a TV
OL,18,Faerial or satellite dish.
OL,3,CState of play: a UK IP-TV switchover
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S     G3/13
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34204
SC,0004
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F342A1670850422
OL,5,FThe answer to the IP-switchover
OL,6,Fconundrum could be DVB-I and 5G
OL,7,FBroadcast ` giving viewers free access
OL,8,Fto content regardless of their
OL,9,Fbroadband supplier.
OL,11,FDVB-I support within TV receivers would
OL,12,Fallow viewers to access a channel list
OL,13,Fthat can include a variety of sources
OL,14,Fduring the inevitable transition
OL,15,Fperiod.
OL,3,CState of play: a UK IP-TV switchover
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S     G4/13
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34205
SC,0005
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F342A1670850422
OL,5,FSay for example ITV decided to switch
OL,6,FITV 2 from terrestrial to IP. A TV with
OL,7,FDVB-I support would automatically
OL,8,Fswitch from accessing the terrestrial
OL,9,Fversion of the channel to the IP
OL,10,Fversion on the day of the transition.
OL,11,FThe viewer, providing of course they
OL,12,Fhave an internet connection, would not
OL,13,Fnotice any difference.
OL,3,CState of play: a UK IP-TV switchover
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S     G5/13
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34206
SC,0006
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F342A1670850422
OL,5,FIt could be done in a more subtle way
OL,6,Fin advance of any transition: the TV
OL,7,Fcould opt for the SD ITV 2 signal from
OL,8,FFreeview if there was no internet
OL,9,Fconnection. Otherwise, it would be told
OL,10,Fto prefer the HD ITV 2 stream by
OL,11,Fdefault. You could end up with viewers
OL,12,Fmigrating to internet TV without
OL,13,Frealising it.
OL,3,CState of play: a UK IP-TV switchover
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S     G6/13
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34207
SC,0007
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F342A1670850422
OL,5,FBT has started something similar, but
OL,6,Fit is not an open format available on
OL,7,Fany receiver. Neither will it combine a
OL,8,Fmixture of both terrestrial and online.
OL,9,FIf you go to internet mode on BT's Pro
OL,10,Fboxes you forfeit access to some
OL,11,Fterrestrial channels. If you opt for
OL,12,Faerial mode, you don't get access to
OL,13,Fextra HD channels that are only
OL,14,Fstreamed.
OL,16,FEarlier this year Together, the former
OL,17,FCommunity Channel, switched to online
OL,18,Fdelivery of its main channel. This
OL,19,Fmeant compatible TVs automatically
OL,20,Fswitched to an online TV feed.
OL,21,FNon-compatible TVs saw a caption.
OL,3,CState of play: a UK IP-TV switchover
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S     G7/13
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34208
SC,0008
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F342A1670850422
OL,5,FThis was done by an HbbTV application.
OL,6,FFor this to work, a compatible TV needs
OL,7,Fa terrestrial TV signal to receive the
OL,8,Finstructions from the HbbTV app when
OL,9,Fthe channel is selected from the
OL,10,Fchannel list.
OL,12,FIn fact, most Freeview Play apps work
OL,13,Fon the same basis. No terrestrial
OL,14,Freception, no access, even if you have
OL,15,Fa working internet connection. That's
OL,16,Fwhy Freeview Play, in its current
OL,17,Fincarnation, wouldn't be suitable for
OL,18,Fan IP-switchover.
OL,3,CState of play: a UK IP-TV switchover
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S     G8/13
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34209
SC,0009
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F342A1670850422
OL,5,FDVB-I could do this without needing an
OL,6,Funderlying terrestrial TV signal. But
OL,7,Fyou could still use HbbTV apps to
OL,8,Fprovide viewers with additional data
OL,9,Fand red button services.
OL,11,FIncidentally, Together complained to
OL,12,FOfcom that it had received hundreds of
OL,13,Fcomplaints from viewers who had
OL,14,Fnon-compatible devices. The channel has
OL,15,Fsince secured regular broadcast
OL,16,Fcapacity to allow it to continue
OL,17,Fbroadcasting a terrestrial service.
OL,18,FTogether+1 currently still uses the
OL,19,FHbbTV app to stream through the day.
OL,3,CState of play: a UK IP-TV switchover
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S     G9/13
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34210
SC,0010
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F342A1670850422
OL,5,F5G Broadcast would operate in a
OL,6,FReceive-Only Mode (ROM), be free-to-air
OL,7,Fand wouldn't need a SIM card (SIM-free
OL,8,Freception). It would use the current
OL,9,FUHF frequencies used by terrestrial TV.
OL,11,FDuring a transition, it would be able
OL,12,Fto operate side-by-side on adjacent
OL,13,Ffrequencies without interference ` that
OL,14,Fwas confirmed in Hamburg where 5G
OL,15,FBroadcast was broadcast alongside
OL,16,Fcurrent terrestrial TV multiplexes.
OL,3,CState of play: a UK IP-TV switchover
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S    G10/13
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34211
SC,0011
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F342A1670850422
OL,5,FAn opportunity to try this out in the
OL,6,FUK could occur from 2026, if the BBC
OL,7,Fopted to end its licence for multiplex
OL,8,FPSB3 (the HD multiplex). When asked by
OL,9,Fthe DCMS, the BBC was the only
OL,10,Fmultiplex licence holder not eager to
OL,11,Frenew its licence when it expires, as
OL,12,Fit wanted to see how things would
OL,13,Fdevelop.
OL,15,FThe HD multiplex would not be needed if
OL,16,FSD services were withdrawn: the HD
OL,17,Fchannels could move over to take their
OL,18,Fspace. The frequencies used by PSB3
OL,19,Fcould then be used to trial 5G
OL,20,FBroadcast.
OL,3,CState of play: a UK IP-TV switchover
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S    G11/13
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34212
SC,0012
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F342A1670850422
OL,5,FAnd Arqiva ` who would otherwise end up
OL,6,Fwith lots of redudant masts around the
OL,7,Fcountry ` would see their masts and
OL,8,Frelays join together to create a 5G
OL,9,FBroadcast network ` a bit like a giant
OL,10,Fmesh network to carry the signal.
OL,12,FRemoving SD simulcasts of the main
OL,13,Fchannels in 2026 would be an ideal way
OL,14,Fto get IP-compatible devices into
OL,15,Fviewer's homes.
OL,17,FIt would act as a prompt to get viewers
OL,18,Fwith the oldest equipment up-to-date
OL,19,Fwith developments.
OL,3,CState of play: a UK IP-TV switchover
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S    G12/13
OL,2,W+.!+,"-$/*%/*% / "-$+,*-'U(,,,,,,,,,,,,
PN,34213
SC,0013
PS,c000
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F342A1670850422
OL,5,FWhere viewers updated their TV but
OL,6,Fdidn't have online access, Freeview
OL,7,Freception would continue as before, but
OL,8,Fwith HD-only versions of the main five
OL,9,Fchannels. As soon as the TV was
OL,10,Fconnected to fibre or mobile or even 5G
OL,11,FBroadcast, it would automatically
OL,12,Fchoose the IP delivered versions over
OL,13,Fthe terrestrial versions.
OL,3,CState of play: a UK IP-TV switchover
OL,1,W~+$ hw1~{4~k4 ~shw1~sj7}  S    G13/13
